1
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,640
EXPOSE

2
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:57,400
Your payment

3
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,640
is to expose evil.

4
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,640
Fine.

5
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:01,520
There's no way he'll make it.

6
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,920
Once the video ends,
they'll find out for sure.

7
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,880
I, Praab Fah Sang Din,

8
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:14,520
see fate through destiny cards.

9
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,280
- Destiny cards? I've never heard of that.
- Yes.

10
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:20,360
- It sounds amazing.
- Can I ask about anything?

11
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,280
LET'S GO CLEANSE YOUR BAD LUCK. WAYU

12
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:25,360
But I still don't get it.
Why did you bring me here?

13
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,560
Do you want to understand?

14
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,240
Wanna try racing with a substitute?

15
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,280
Wow, it's so beautiful.

16
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:45,920
Ms. Fahsai.

17
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,520
Mr. Dharn?

18
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,680
What are you doing here?

19
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,440
This is my friend, Suthee.

20
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,480
- Hello.
- He invited me.

21
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,120
We're planning to develop
the community and this area.

22
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:07,600
I never thought I'd run into you here.
What a lucky coincidence.

23
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:21,560
I've booked a restaurant for 4 p.m.
See you then.

24
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,520
Okay.

25
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,600
I'll be waiting.

26
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,120
Alright.

27
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:45,200
You brought me here
to meet Mr. Dharn on purpose?

28
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:52,280
Do you like this place?
Did you enjoy kayaking?

29
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,360
Yes.

30
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,000
But you still haven't answered me.

31
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,920
I just wanted to take you out
to do something fun

32
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,720
and relax, take your mind off things.

33
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:08,720
As for Mr. Dharn, I think
his development plan is interesting.

34
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,560
You could even use

35
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:15,400
your kayak substitute team experience
to help him.

36
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:20,200
Who asked you to meddle this much?

37
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:24,440
If you don't want to see him, that's fine.

38
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,960
Just think of it as a trip to relax.

39
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,800
But it'd be a shame, though.

40
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:34,880
I even bought you a dress for dinner.

41
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,040
Yes, bro.

42
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,640
Yes.

43
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:54,880
Yes.

44
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:04,360
I got the photos. Any specific ones
you want me to highlight?

45
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,240
Pick what works and handle it.

46
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,360
Got it.

47
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:11,920
Thank you, Minister Chukiat,
for supporting my project.

48
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:17,600
No, I should be thanking you
for explaining its benefits.

49
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:20,240
Alright.

50
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,560
Where are you going?

51
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,720
That's rude, Samut.

52
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:47,400
I have an urgent matter to take care of.

53
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:52,920
Please enjoy Heaven's Club, sir.

54
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,480
I'll take my leave.

55
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:09,640
Never thought I'd get
to have a meal with you like this.

56
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,560
Actually, I wanted to visit you
at the foundation,

57
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,120
but your secretary
said you hadn't returned yet.

58
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:27,720
I'm sorry I couldn't help you.

59
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,440
It's not your fault.

60
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,920
I kind of know why.

61
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:47,960
Even if we can't work together,

62
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:52,760
we can still do our own parts well.

63
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:58,960
That's true. You're not wrong about that.

64
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:03,000
But what's wrong with working together?

65
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:10,840
Why should politics divide us?

66
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,360
When I worked with you,

67
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,680
I had hope…

68
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:21,960
that we could break down
that meaningless wall.

69
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,400
Can't we?

70
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,919
If you just say yes,

71
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:37,039
I'll handle everything,

72
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:41,480
your brother, your party.

73
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,320
I'll make them accept us.

74
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,920
And more importantly,

75
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,560
it's not just about work.

76
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:04,120
I don't want to lose you.

77
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:22,200
- Hey! Stay away from my sister!
- Samut!

78
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:27,000
Sir, please don't fight. Please calm down.

79
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,720
Please calm down.

80
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:43,920
Fahsai, come with me.

81
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,520
Now.

82
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,800
Get in the car.

83
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:09,480
- Get out of the car.
- I'm going home.

84
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:15,200
Don't think you can act like this
and I'll forget everything.

85
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,640
Get out, Fahsai.

86
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,760
- Samut, I'm not going.
- Fahsai.

87
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,080
- Get out.
- I'm not going. I'm not talking.

88
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:28,000
Let go, Samut.

89
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,520
Let go. I'm not talking.

90
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,280
- Samut!
- Come here.

91
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,320
Let go!

92
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,200
- We need to settle this right now, Fahsai.
- Samut.

93
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,080
I have nothing to talk to you about.

94
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,960
You need to apologize to Mr. Dharn
for punching him like that.

95
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,080
Why did you do that?

96
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:48,080
You still have the nerve to ask me that?

97
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:51,560
Sneaking off to see a man like this,
right under my nose.

98
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:55,480
If I hadn't gotten there in time,
who knows where he would've taken you.

99
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:58,480
I wasn't sneaking around.
I just happened to run into him.

100
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,240
Just happened to?

101
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:03,720
What do you take me for?
Think you can lie to me that easily?

102
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,960
If you won't believe me,

103
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:09,200
then we have nothing to talk about.

104
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:14,080
Fahsai, I heard him say
he couldn't bear to lose you.

105
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,040
Hey.

106
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,360
He has a hidden agenda.

107
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:21,800
So you are not to contact him,
and you are not to see him again.

108
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:22,840
Understand?

109
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,520
Do you like him? Hm?

110
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:32,280
That politician from the other side,
do you like him?

111
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,120
If I like Mr. Dharn,
then that's my business.

112
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,040
Don't say that, Fahsai.

113
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,960
Don't let him use you.

114
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,840
You're underestimating me.

115
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,840
I'm not a child anymore.

116
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,640
You have no right to order me around
or force me like this.

117
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,560
Right. You're not a child.

118
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,560
I know that.

119
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,120
I know better than anyone.

120
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:08,440
Looks like you still don't know
what you did wrong.

121
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,160
I'll tell you.

122
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,120
No matter what man you secretly go see,

123
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,800
you will never be out of my sight again.

124
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:42,280
I will never let you run off

125
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:45,680
with those men.

126
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:54,080
They will never get the chance
to touch even the tip of your fingernail.

127
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,520
Be careful…

128
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,840
You are not allowed to be with any man.

129
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:27,080
Understand?

130
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:40,360
Pit, call Si.

131
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,680
<i>Track Mahasamut's car now.</i>

132
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:46,920
Got it, bro.

133
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,440
Based on your current GPS signal…

134
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,360
BEACH AREA - BANGKOK

135
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:55,920
…if you go left, the area leads to hotels,
resorts, and vacation homes.

136
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,760
If you go right,
that's the road back into the city.

137
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:03,240
Bangkok or the beach?

138
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,240
<i>Sam, hack the highway cameras</i>

139
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:09,560
<i>and check where Mahasamut's car went.</i>

140
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:19,120
I don't see any trace of his car, bro.

141
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,560
Did I choose the wrong road?

142
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:25,480
But I think it'll be fine, bro.

143
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,640
Samut's already furious at Dharn,
just like we planned.

144
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:31,840
Once we release the clip of the punch,
it'll be chaos for sure.

145
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:35,640
No matter how much
he argued with Ms. Fahsai,

146
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,640
they're still siblings.

147
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,320
He clearly loves his sister to death.

148
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,280
I don't think
it'll get that serious, right?

149
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,200
Yeah.

150
00:15:57,480 --> 00:16:01,000
I'm turning back to that intersection.
You guys keep looking for the car.

151
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,120
Got it.

152
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,800
SATTAHIP, RAYONG, JOMTIEN BEACH PATTAYA

153
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:18,320
Samut, let go. It's uncomfortable.

154
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,600
So you can secretly meet Dharn just fine,

155
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:32,160
but being with me makes you uncomfortable?

156
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:36,680
I'm your sister.

157
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:47,320
This is Fahsai, your sister.

158
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:55,240
Since when do I have a sister?

159
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:00,680
Whoever you sleep with,

160
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:04,319
however many kids you have,
that's your business.

161
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,319
Oh?

162
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:10,760
But she is not staying here.

163
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,920
Hey, Fahsai's mother passed away.

164
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:22,800
I only have one daughter left now.
That means you two are siblings.

165
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,720
Samut!

166
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,160
Don't take it personally.

167
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:39,320
Samut's mother died a long time ago,

168
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,000
so that's why he's like this.

169
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:45,440
Just keep being kind to him.
He'll come around.

170
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,240
Yes.

171
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:57,800
Samut.

172
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,880
I made porridge for you.

173
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:07,080
Samut. Come on, get up and eat.

174
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,600
Your sister made it for you.

175
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:13,520
Get up and eat.

176
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:17,240
Come on.

177
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:43,400
Samut, wait.

178
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,880
You're still not fully well.

179
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,040
Please don't go out.

180
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:51,120
I'm begging you, Samut.

181
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,920
Dad told me to look after you.

182
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,600
Samut.

183
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:58,880
Samut! Samut!

184
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:02,240
You think you're tough?

185
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,640
Stop!

186
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,000
Don't hurt my brother.

187
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,480
- What?
- Don't hurt my brother.

188
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:16,000
He's not well right now. I'm sorry.

189
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:18,040
Teach your brother how to behave.

190
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,600
I'm letting this go
because of your sister.

191
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,000
What a mood killer.

192
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,800
Samut.

193
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:33,840
Slowly, okay?

194
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,160
You should never have come into my life.

195
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:01,240
And you definitely should never
have been so kind to me.

196
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:09,560
Samut, are you okay?

197
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,480
I'm fine.

198
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:23,840
Samut, slowly.

199
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,000
Easy.

200
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:17,200
You made me love you.

201
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,800
I love you more than anyone.

202
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:33,000
More than any man ever could.

203
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:40,160
But I…

204
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,240
I have no right to you at all.

205
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:52,680
Do you even realize what you're saying?

206
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,800
Let go of me. I want to go home.

207
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,760
We can talk about this at home later.

208
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:03,000
Fahsai.

209
00:23:06,840 --> 00:23:07,840
Fahsai.

210
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,280
Fahsai.

211
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,920
Fahsai.

212
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,720
Fahsai, you can't do this to me.

213
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,880
Are you running from me to go to that man?

214
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:27,520
Samut, stop! We're brother and sister.

215
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,360
You're my brother.

216
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,840
- Don't do this, please.
- Fahsai.

217
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:33,400
Fahsai, you're the one
who made me become like this.

218
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:37,280
- I can't take it anymore, Fahsai.
- I didn't do anything.

219
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:38,560
Fahsai.

220
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:41,960
I never once meant to hurt you. Never.

221
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:47,800
- Fahsai, come here.
- Let go.

222
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:51,840
- I told you to get back inside.
- Let go! Help!

223
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:55,160
You dare do this to me?

224
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,400
I told you not to make me do this.

225
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:00,440
- Huh?
- Help!

226
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:01,760
Fahsai!

227
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,960
I'm circling the beach now.

228
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:10,600
Pitbull, we've got new info.

229
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,080
What is it?

230
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,840
Mahasamut has a vacation house
around there.

231
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:16,680
Send me the location.

232
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:32,080
Hey, bro.

233
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:34,240
Curve ahead! Curve! Curve!

234
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,160
Fahsai!

235
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:49,160
- Fahsai!
- Let go! Stop!

236
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:51,840
Fahsai!

237
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:04,960
Fahsai.

238
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:09,480
Fahsai, are you okay? Take a deep breath.

239
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:12,440
Calm down.

240
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,920
Breathe.

241
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,240
Where is the medicine?

242
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,000
Where do I get it?

243
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:29,000
There's nothing here. Fahsai.

244
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:30,680
Fahsai!

245
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,040
I found Samut's car.

246
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:50,560
Fahsai!

247
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:57,920
Fahsai! Why are you running away?

248
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,000
Ms. Fahsai.

249
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:11,520
Ms. Fahsai.

250
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:21,600
Fahsai!

251
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:35,520
Listen to me first.

252
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,240
Fahsai.

253
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,080
Are you okay?

254
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:49,640
Why are you running from me?

255
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,640
You and I still have a score to settle.

256
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:06,840
But right now,
I want to talk to my sister.

257
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:16,040
You dare?

258
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,120
I'm the one who brought Fahsai here.

259
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,000
I'll be the one taking her back.

260
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,720
Are you sure you want to do this?

261
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:08,560
If I shoot,

262
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,560
at this range,

263
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,520
I won't miss.

264
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,440
So what's it gonna be?

265
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,360
What's it gonna be?

266
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:35,840
I'm sorry if I've upset you.

267
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:39,800
But Fahsai looks unwell.

268
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,440
I want to get her home first.

269
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:45,360
As for us,

270
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,240
we can settle it afterward.

271
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:55,240
You really don't understand
a damn thing, do you?

272
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:57,000
Hey!

273
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:01,920
Are you insane?

274
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:04,120
Can't you see your sister is right here?

275
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:12,720
If you don't stop this madness right now,

276
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:16,120
come on then. Shoot me!

277
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:19,720
Shoot me!

278
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:27,360
Take the gun away.

279
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:31,800
Give him the gun!

280
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:03,440
Fahsai…

281
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,640
It's alright. It's alright.

282
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:15,480
You're safe now.

283
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:21,920
It's alright.

284
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:37,680
Calm down.

285
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:44,440
It's alright.

286
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:48,000
It's alright.

287
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:59,160
- Sergeant.
- Yes?

288
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:00,960
- So what happened?
- Captain.

289
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:02,960
Ms. Aemika has already fled the country.

290
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,600
I think

291
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:09,280
there must have been a vehicle switch
at a blind spot with no CCTV.

292
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:13,200
The way she ran from you like that,
it's definitely not normal.

293
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:16,840
At first, I only thought
she might be hiding something.

294
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:20,680
But after what I saw,
she's clearly been threatened.

295
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,440
There's something being covered up.

296
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:30,000
Yes, sir. I think we need
to keep investigating quietly.

297
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:34,640
Captain, what about Ms. Prapai
showing up just in time to help you?

298
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:35,800
What was that about?

299
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:43,320
- You want to know?
- Yes.

300
00:31:57,160 --> 00:32:00,480
<i>We tracked down a witness,</i>
<i>and still got absolutely nowhere, Captain.</i>

301
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:03,240
Exactly, Sergeant. Total waste of time.

302
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:06,920
Six years ago, I was forbidden
from investigating the Jaiaree case,

303
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,880
so it's always bothered me.

304
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:10,360
But now,

305
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:13,320
if there's nothing, then fine.
I won't have to waste any more time.

306
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:15,160
Are you even a real cop?

307
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:17,640
The witness fled
and you're just going to let it go?

308
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:20,280
Captain, but it's pretty surprising

309
00:32:20,360 --> 00:32:22,240
that Ms. Prapai happened to run into you

310
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,800
<i>and save you at exactly the right moment.</i>

311
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:29,240
Sergeant, honestly,

312
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:30,960
do you really think all of this

313
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:32,840
was just a coincidence?

314
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:35,080
Whoa! What do you mean, Captain?

315
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:44,400
There's no such thing
as that much coincidence in this world.

316
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:51,040
I only just realized it myself

317
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:54,120
that I'm actually that hot.

318
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:56,920
Whoa, hold on.

319
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:00,320
Captain, are you saying Ms. Prapai

320
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:02,240
is into you?

321
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:03,360
<i>Come on, Sergeant.</i>

322
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:05,440
I don't even want to put it that way,

323
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:07,960
but the situation…

324
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:09,880
It really does look like that.

325
00:33:09,960 --> 00:33:11,280
- You know what?
- What is it, sir?

326
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:13,120
- Ever since the first time I met her,
- Yes?

327
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:16,160
she was already giving me those looks.

328
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:18,400
Wink, wink, like this.

329
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:20,880
- Really?
- I got goosebumps all over.

330
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,520
- Really?
- And after that,

331
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:25,640
<i>she kept trying to get close to me,</i>
<i>asking for my help.</i>

332
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:29,160
Out of all the women
who've ever come on to me in my life,

333
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:30,960
Ms. Prapai

334
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:35,320
has come on the strongest.

335
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:37,920
You…

336
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:42,720
You…

337
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:45,160
You narcissistic idiot.

338
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:48,440
You're way too full of yourself.

339
00:33:57,360 --> 00:33:58,480
For now,

340
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:01,320
you should go stay
at your condo for a while.

341
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:03,120
I want to talk to Fahsai.

342
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:05,080
How many more times do you want
to put your sister through this?

343
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:09,000
Dad, I hadn't even done anything yet.

344
00:34:09,639 --> 00:34:13,159
When I took her to that house,
I just wanted to talk.

345
00:34:13,239 --> 00:34:14,520
Just talk?

346
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:19,639
Then why was she running barefoot,
trying to get away from you?

347
00:34:21,920 --> 00:34:23,520
Because we couldn't talk things through.

348
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:24,960
You…

349
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:30,040
Do you think I didn't know all this time?

350
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:34,719
I saw the way you looked at Fahsai.

351
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:39,679
I already knew what you were thinking.

352
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:43,440
But I saw that you had Maysa.

353
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:44,880
You've also got women at that club.

354
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,159
You're not lacking anything.

355
00:34:46,239 --> 00:34:47,960
So why did you
have to involve your sister?

356
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:50,600
Those women are just people I sleep with.

357
00:34:52,199 --> 00:34:53,760
Just that.

358
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:59,320
Fahsai is not like that.
She's not like those women, Dad.

359
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,720
I love Fahsai.

360
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,080
How dare you say that out loud?

361
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:13,440
You're sick.

362
00:35:13,520 --> 00:35:15,640
And whose fault is it
that I turned out like this?

363
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:18,440
Yours.

364
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:21,200
You were the one who brought Fahsai here.

365
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,040
A sister?

366
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:26,680
I'd never even met her before.

367
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,480
And then she was kind to me.

368
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:35,320
And I fell in love with her.

369
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:39,600
You should never have let
those disgusting thoughts come out at all.

370
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:44,960
Right now,

371
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,840
it's too late.

372
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:51,720
There is no way Fahsai
will ever look at you the same again.

373
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:55,880
You've destroyed
all of her love and trust in you.

374
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:52,680
Damn it.

375
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,040
I didn't think he could be that evil.

376
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:58,000
You know what?

377
00:36:58,080 --> 00:37:00,760
More than half of rape cases are committed

378
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,920
by someone close to the victim.
Someone in the family.

379
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:07,520
I feel bad for Ms. Fahsai.

380
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:15,040
Are you sure this wasn't
what you were planning from the start?

381
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:23,360
Come on, Pud. Again?

382
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,960
Every time it's about women,
you get worked up.

383
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:29,720
He didn't want this to happen either.

384
00:37:32,200 --> 00:37:34,600
Even if that whole family
is a burden on society.

385
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:41,880
We just wanted to make Mahasamut angry.

386
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,440
But in the end,

387
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:46,080
the woman is the one who gets hurt.

388
00:37:47,680 --> 00:37:49,200
The plan worked.

389
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,600
Congratulations.

390
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:09,720
If you're going to expose those bastards,

391
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:13,040
stop letting every little distraction
throw you off.

392
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:30,240
Samut.

393
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,360
I think karma's starting
to catch up with them.

394
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:15,720
But it's still nowhere near enough
for what they did to you.

395
00:41:19,080 --> 00:41:21,000
Don't let what happened to my family

396
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:22,760
turn you cruel too.

397
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,240
Since when did you become so soft-hearted?

398
00:41:29,440 --> 00:41:31,080
Don't tell me you're going easy on Fahsai?

399
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:40,600
Mm.

400
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,800
I just didn't think it would go this far.

401
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:49,040
I thought Mahasamut would just get angry.

402
00:41:52,880 --> 00:41:55,280
I didn't think he'd abduct his own sister.

403
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:59,720
That's exactly why someone like him
deserves to be exposed.

404
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:02,280
We still don't have proof about that.

405
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:04,440
- But if it's about something else--
- Oh.

406
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:07,400
There's something you should know.

407
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:12,040
Captain Anawin is investigating
the Jaiaree family case.

408
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:20,000
If he really wants to dig into it,

409
00:42:20,080 --> 00:42:21,120
what do you think?

410
00:42:30,680 --> 00:42:33,240
The bullet matches
the model listed in the report.

411
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:42,400
The last witness has disappeared.

412
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:48,560
Captain, someone left this for you.

413
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:02,920
MR. PHOB HOMCHUI

414
00:43:14,560 --> 00:43:18,320
MR. PHOB HOMCHUI

415
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:29,120
Why haven't you eaten?

416
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:34,600
Fahsai.

417
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,400
You can relax now.

418
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:40,600
It's just the two of us
in this house at the moment.

419
00:43:41,120 --> 00:43:43,240
I made your brother go stay
at the condo for a while.

420
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,360
He has campaign preparations to do anyway,

421
00:43:46,440 --> 00:43:48,760
and it's closer to party headquarters.

422
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:57,520
About yesterday,

423
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:02,320
your brother didn't mean it.

424
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:06,760
He was just worried about you.

425
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:11,160
<i>You made me love you.</i>

426
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:14,120
I love you more than anyone.

427
00:44:17,560 --> 00:44:19,960
More than any man ever could.

428
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:24,800
But I…

429
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:30,080
I have no right to you at all.

430
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:41,360
Fahsai,

431
00:44:43,760 --> 00:44:45,800
Samut is your brother.

432
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:49,040
He would never think badly of you.

433
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:53,880
What happened yesterday, you were both

434
00:44:55,120 --> 00:44:59,560
just caught up in your emotions,
so you couldn't talk things through.

435
00:45:13,480 --> 00:45:15,520
Is that what Samut told you?

436
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:22,400
Yes.

437
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:24,760
He just

438
00:45:26,080 --> 00:45:29,200
lost control in a moment of anger,
that's all.

439
00:45:30,600 --> 00:45:34,400
But he promised me it won't happen again.

440
00:45:36,840 --> 00:45:38,560
Don't think too much about it.

441
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:41,320
There's nothing to worry about anymore.

442
00:45:45,400 --> 00:45:46,840
Come on, eat something.

443
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:52,640
I'm not eating.

444
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:59,120
I want to be alone.
Please let me be alone.

445
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:12,960
Wayu.

446
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:19,800
Fahsai is resting.

447
00:46:21,160 --> 00:46:24,800
I'll let her know you came
to visit when she wakes up.

448
00:46:27,320 --> 00:46:29,800
And about yesterday,
I need to apologize on Samut's behalf.

449
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:31,560
He went too far.

450
00:46:32,360 --> 00:46:34,280
And why should you apologize to him?

451
00:46:35,760 --> 00:46:38,400
He's the one
who took Fahsai to meet Dharn.

452
00:46:39,600 --> 00:46:42,440
This whole mess happened because of him.

453
00:46:43,120 --> 00:46:45,000
But you knew perfectly well, didn't you,

454
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:49,080
that Ms. Fahsai
asked Mrs. Jaratsri to help her?

455
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:51,520
I only looked after her after that.

456
00:46:51,600 --> 00:46:54,840
As her guard.
I had to follow her orders, that's all.

457
00:46:54,920 --> 00:46:57,720
Then why didn't you report it to me?

458
00:46:58,800 --> 00:47:02,520
Your job was to stop Fahsai
from meeting Dharn.

459
00:47:02,600 --> 00:47:03,720
What was so hard about that?

460
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:05,560
But if I got on bad terms with her,

461
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:08,720
I wouldn't be able
to stay by her side and protect her.

462
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:12,680
So I had to give in.

463
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:16,320
I planned to get her out
once I had the chance.

464
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:20,840
That matches what Jaratsri said.

465
00:47:25,480 --> 00:47:29,560
Besides, how could Wayu
force Fahsai to do anything?

466
00:47:29,640 --> 00:47:30,680
He's not like you.

467
00:47:32,640 --> 00:47:35,960
Alright then. You go home first.
I'll let Fahsai know.

468
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:41,440
Yes, sir. If there's anything
I can help with, just let me know.

469
00:47:42,160 --> 00:47:43,640
What else would we ask you to help with

470
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:45,920
when this is what happens after?

471
00:47:47,720 --> 00:47:49,040
Samut.

472
00:47:54,320 --> 00:47:55,360
I'll take my leave now.

473
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:16,560
Still?

474
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:19,520
You're still making trouble for yourself.

475
00:48:21,280 --> 00:48:23,440
If Wayu didn't want that piece of land,

476
00:48:23,520 --> 00:48:25,840
he would've gone after you yesterday

477
00:48:26,440 --> 00:48:27,760
after you pulled a gun on him.

478
00:48:27,840 --> 00:48:30,080
Stop talking about him already, Dad.

479
00:48:33,080 --> 00:48:34,600
Can I talk to Fahsai yet?

480
00:48:35,520 --> 00:48:38,280
Do you think she'll even talk to you?

481
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:41,240
She won't even talk to me.

482
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:44,040
Just go. Go do your work.

483
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:46,840
I'll handle Fahsai.

484
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:09,760
- Fahsai.
- Mr. Samut.

485
00:49:09,840 --> 00:49:12,000
Fahsai, please listen to me first.

486
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:15,800
About yesterday, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to do that.

487
00:49:15,880 --> 00:49:17,440
I just got angry

488
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:19,640
and I scared you.

489
00:49:22,720 --> 00:49:24,240
I promise I won't…

490
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:29,240
I promise I won't do that again.

491
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:39,840
- Fahsai, don't do this.
- Don't.

492
00:49:41,800 --> 00:49:43,680
- I'm begging you. Don't avoid me--
- Don't.

493
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:49,000
I'm sorry.

494
00:49:51,520 --> 00:49:53,400
- Can you forgive me?
- Don't come any closer.

495
00:50:02,400 --> 00:50:04,320
We've always loved each other.

496
00:50:08,760 --> 00:50:10,360
Can we go back to the way things were?

497
00:50:15,720 --> 00:50:16,760
Please.

498
00:50:18,880 --> 00:50:21,000
- Fahsai, I'm really sorry.
- Don't come closer!

499
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:24,000
I don't want to talk. Get out.

500
00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:24,960
Get out!

501
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:29,080
Get out!

502
00:50:34,560 --> 00:50:35,600
Samut.

503
00:50:47,280 --> 00:50:50,080
I told you to go back.

504
00:50:52,120 --> 00:50:53,320
Sir,

505
00:50:54,160 --> 00:50:57,280
usually, Ms. Fahsai helps out
with Mr. Samut's campaign team.

506
00:50:58,120 --> 00:51:00,440
If she doesn't join in,

507
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:03,280
people will say our party has a problem.

508
00:51:05,560 --> 00:51:07,640
And whose fault is that?

509
00:51:08,240 --> 00:51:09,640
You have to help me, Dad.

510
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:12,840
You have to help make Fahsai
stop being angry with me.

511
00:51:14,080 --> 00:51:16,320
You can't just let the two of us
end up like this.

512
00:51:53,680 --> 00:51:54,840
Hey.

513
00:51:55,520 --> 00:51:57,920
What's wrong? Been watching
too many horror movies or what?

514
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:02,880
I didn't know doctors
were scared of ghosts too.

515
00:52:03,640 --> 00:52:05,560
If I weren't, I would've
become a doctor for people.

516
00:52:08,360 --> 00:52:09,920
What now? Be quiet.

517
00:52:14,480 --> 00:52:15,600
Hello, Uncle.

518
00:52:16,360 --> 00:52:19,400
- Are you Uncle Phop?
- Yes.

519
00:52:26,240 --> 00:52:30,240
You're the undertaker
who handled the bodies

520
00:52:30,320 --> 00:52:32,200
from the Jaiaree family case
back then, right?

521
00:52:34,080 --> 00:52:37,360
Can you tell me more
about the condition of the bodies

522
00:52:37,440 --> 00:52:40,920
than what's written in this report?

523
00:52:44,480 --> 00:52:45,480
Here.

524
00:52:49,320 --> 00:52:50,760
Keep your mouth shut.

525
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:56,720
I would never say a word

526
00:52:56,800 --> 00:52:59,600
that with a deformed wrist like that,

527
00:53:00,440 --> 00:53:03,080
there's no way that body
could belong to a surgeon.

528
00:53:07,000 --> 00:53:09,200
I mean, I was just joking, sir.

529
00:53:18,880 --> 00:53:20,080
Look here, sir.

530
00:53:20,600 --> 00:53:22,920
The body was burned to a crisp,
like charcoal.

531
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:24,920
There was nothing left to identify.

532
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:26,800
But the report says

533
00:53:27,400 --> 00:53:30,880
the time of the incident
and the time the police found the body

534
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:32,440
were only a few minutes apart.

535
00:53:33,680 --> 00:53:36,280
Doesn't it seem strange that the body
was already burned that badly?

536
00:53:41,000 --> 00:53:43,920
Hello? Oh, yes, we have large coffins.

537
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:47,200
Just a moment. I'll go check for you.

538
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:50,520
Excuse me. I need to get back to work.

539
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:52,840
Just a moment, please.

540
00:53:53,840 --> 00:53:55,480
He's not going to be any help, is he?

541
00:53:57,640 --> 00:53:59,560
You want to hear something even stranger?

542
00:54:00,280 --> 00:54:02,160
Back when he was just an undertaker,

543
00:54:02,760 --> 00:54:04,840
right after handling Peeraka's body,

544
00:54:05,560 --> 00:54:07,880
he opened this coffin shop
almost immediately.

545
00:54:09,320 --> 00:54:10,400
Really?

546
00:54:13,480 --> 00:54:14,840
Then wait a second.

547
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:27,960
Hey. I need you
to handle something for me.

548
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:39,320
Do these look familiar, Uncle?

549
00:54:40,400 --> 00:54:42,720
These are the things
you sold on the black market

550
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:45,160
back when you were still an undertaker.

551
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:48,160
Everyone knows
you stole them from the corpse.

552
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:52,560
Did Thong tell you that?

553
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:57,400
Damn it. He shouldn't
have sold me out like that.

554
00:54:58,400 --> 00:55:00,240
We split the profits fifty-fifty.

555
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:06,840
Wait, who exactly are you people?

556
00:55:07,360 --> 00:55:09,520
If you cooperate with the police,

557
00:55:09,600 --> 00:55:11,160
your sentence can become lighter.

558
00:55:16,800 --> 00:55:20,920
So what's the truth about Peeraka's body?

559
00:55:27,440 --> 00:55:28,400
Wait.

560
00:55:29,640 --> 00:55:31,040
Just give me a second.

561
00:55:55,920 --> 00:55:58,120
Right on plan.

562
00:55:58,200 --> 00:56:00,440
Captain Anawin followed the lead
and got results.

563
00:56:00,520 --> 00:56:03,600
Now all that's left is getting what's
inside that box from Phop for examination.

564
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:05,400
With only that evidence,

565
00:56:05,960 --> 00:56:08,600
the case is moving along
pretty fast. Not bad.

566
00:56:18,400 --> 00:56:20,960
Now there's something else I'm wondering.

567
00:56:21,640 --> 00:56:23,760
Why didn't Captain Anawin say anything

568
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:26,360
when he caught me following him?

569
00:56:26,440 --> 00:56:28,560
He even let me join the investigation.

570
00:56:29,160 --> 00:56:30,560
What's he thinking?

571
00:56:34,440 --> 00:56:36,240
If he wasn't suspicious at all,

572
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:39,880
didn't it cross your mind
that maybe he likes you?

573
00:56:42,720 --> 00:56:44,880
For men,

574
00:56:45,480 --> 00:56:47,960
if they don't have any business with you
but keep getting involved,

575
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:50,560
there's usually only one reason.

576
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:58,120
Then if Captain Anawin
really does like me,

577
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:00,080
what would you say?

578
00:57:01,920 --> 00:57:03,120
I'd be…

579
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:09,280
okay with it. If he's a good guy.

580
00:57:17,320 --> 00:57:18,960
Okay my ass!

581
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:05,120
PLEASE PICK UP MY CALL

582
00:58:35,400 --> 00:58:38,600
Pulling tricks like this,
I knew it'd be you.

583
00:58:39,200 --> 00:58:40,760
Thought you weren't going to pick up.

584
00:58:42,840 --> 00:58:44,720
Thank you for helping me.

585
00:58:46,440 --> 00:58:48,600
And I'm sorry
for dragging you into trouble.

586
00:58:50,280 --> 00:58:51,240
Trouble?

587
00:58:52,840 --> 00:58:53,720
What trouble?

588
00:58:54,680 --> 00:58:56,680
Getting a break feels great, actually.

589
00:59:00,960 --> 00:59:03,320
Do you have to mess with me
every single day?

590
00:59:05,320 --> 00:59:08,400
If you don't want your lazy subordinate
getting too comfortable,

591
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,400
<i>then you need to eat well,</i>

592
00:59:11,920 --> 00:59:15,080
get proper rest, and maybe exercise a bit.

593
00:59:15,760 --> 00:59:17,320
<i>You'll get better faster.</i>

594
00:59:18,520 --> 00:59:22,040
And don't throw away
my get-well gift, okay?

595
00:59:23,040 --> 00:59:24,040
Get-well gift?

596
00:59:24,120 --> 00:59:25,760
The one you're holding.

597
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:47,720
You…

598
00:59:53,800 --> 00:59:55,920
You left a gift on the balcony?

599
00:59:59,280 --> 01:00:01,080
I didn't want to disturb you.

600
01:00:04,240 --> 01:00:06,240
<i>But I wanted you to know that it means</i>

601
01:00:07,720 --> 01:00:09,640
we're in the same boat now.

602
01:00:17,400 --> 01:00:19,040
I told you before.

603
01:00:21,240 --> 01:00:22,840
I'm on your side.

604
01:00:26,960 --> 01:00:30,720
If you're not ready to see anyone
or talk to anyone yet,

605
01:00:33,080 --> 01:00:34,120
that's okay.

606
01:00:37,640 --> 01:00:39,360
But don't abandon the boat.

607
01:00:42,560 --> 01:00:45,880
Don't forget that

608
01:00:46,720 --> 01:00:48,040
I'm in your boat too.

609
01:01:02,720 --> 01:01:04,120
Thank you.

610
01:01:30,840 --> 01:01:32,080
- Look.
- What's going on?

611
01:01:35,680 --> 01:01:38,240
Hey! What the hell
is that supposed to be?!

612
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:40,080
Are you a boxer or a politician?

613
01:01:40,160 --> 01:01:42,240
<i>If anyone can reach Ms. Fahsai,</i>

614
01:01:42,320 --> 01:01:45,200
<i>please tell her to contact me.</i>

615
01:01:46,560 --> 01:01:48,560
Female patient

616
01:01:48,640 --> 01:01:51,400
suffering psychological trauma
caused by her stepbrother's

617
01:01:51,480 --> 01:01:54,080
inappropriate, incestuous behavior.

618
01:01:58,960 --> 01:02:02,960
Are you sure this won't make Fahsai worse?

619
01:02:03,040 --> 01:02:04,440
I'll take good care of her.

620
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:07,440
I'll teach you how to defend yourselves

621
01:02:07,520 --> 01:02:09,400
against someone physically stronger.

622
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:11,320
You like it when I hold you, don't you?

623
01:03:13,880 --> 01:03:15,880
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
